<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99748669824191></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99748669824191><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1946&mid=99748669824191>high wis items (in general)</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1946&mid=99748669824191#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43244><span id= >prowley</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 10th 7:38 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>People, having 200 wis is nice, but having 200 wis from fewer items is nicer, period.&nbsp;&nbsp;With all my wis gear on I have close to or over 240 wis.  Fact is, I dont wear it all at the same time, I swap in resist gear when that is needed, ac and mana gear most of the time.  In fact currently I run at 199 wis in normal set up - and thats with roughly 100-150 in mana items.<br><br>So, let me tell you, if I got hold of this puppy one of my forest loops goes bye bye, cause frankly, Ill be able to swap in more ac in a slot that is designed for ac.<br><br>Heela<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
